  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "ICT/AV ASSOCIATE",
  "description": "<p>Admin and Financial responsibilities such as budgeting, procurement, inventory and asset management, maintaining usage and loan of ICT and AV equipment. The equipment includes the following and is non-exhaustive:</p><ul><li>Projectors</li><li>Projector Screens</li><li>Patch Panels</li><li>Apple TVs</li><li>Visualisers</li><li>Printers</li><li>Scanners</li><li>Non-SSOE Computing Devices (laptops, Macbooks, iPads)</li><li>Public Address (PA) Systems</li><li>Event Lighting Systems</li><li>Portable Speakers, voice amplification systems</li><li>Microphones</li></ul><p></p><p>Supporting school technology (ICT and AV) planning and operations such as</p><ul><li>providing input or recommendation with regard to equipment choice and placement of ICT and AV equipment</li><li>performing routine checks and preventive maintenance for ICT and AV equipment, maintaining usage and service records of ICT and AV equipment, general trouble shooting of equipment and systems issues, performing minor servicing of ICT and AV equipment</li><li>providing support for NDLP through DMA administration and NDLP Device Clinic</li><li>providing support for e-exams</li><li>providing PA/AV support for regular and special school events, including event lighting, photography, videography and live streaming support</li></ul><p><br />Note:</p><p>The responsibilities outlined above are not exhaustive and may include ad-hoc duties as required.</p>",
